content:
Configure a Custom Client Deployment for Messaging for In-App and Web (Beta)

To enjoy granular control of your web or mobile app messaging experience, create a custom client deployment for Messaging for In-App and Web. This feature is available in Lightning Experience.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience
This article applies to:	Messaging for In-App and Messaging for Web channels

To set up this feature:	
Customize Application
AND
Modify Metadata Through Metadata API Functions

The Messaging for In-App and Web REST API can be used to create conversations that house messaging sessions, generate access tokens, and send messages and files.

Publish a Deployment
Create a custom client deployment that can be referenced in public REST API endpoints.
Complete the steps in Prepare a Salesforce Org for Messaging for In-App and Web:
Configure Omni-Channel.
Create an Omni-Channel flow to route messages.
Create a Messaging for In-App and Web channel on the Messaging Settings page.

Customize Your Deployment
On the Embedded Service Deployment Settings page, customize your deployment by configuring push notifications or preparing a pre-chat form that customers must complete before messaging with an agent.

Reference Your Deployment with the Messaging for In-App and Web REST API
Supply your deployment name when invoking a public endpoint from the Messaging for In-App and Web REST API.

NOTE This feature is a pilot or beta service subject to the Beta Services Terms at Agreements - Salesforce.com.
title: Configuring Custom Client Deployment for Messaging
